et Volt">Chevrolet Volt</a>. The rating for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/All-electric_mode" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"All-electric mo=
de">all-electric mode</a> (left) is expressed in miles per gallon gasoline =
equivalent (mpg).</figcaption></figure>
<p><b>Miles per gallon gasoline equivalent </b> (<b>MPGe</b> or <b>MPG<sub>=
ge</sub></b>) is a measure of the average <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Distance_traveled" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Distance traveled=
">distance traveled</a> per unit of energy consumed. MPGe is used by the <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Environmental_Protecti=
on_Agency" title=3D"United States Environmental Protection Agency">United S=
tates Environmental Protection Agency</a> (EPA) to compare energy consumpti=
on of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alternative_fuel_vehicle" ti=
tle=3D"Alternative fuel vehicle">alternative fuel vehicles</a>, <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plug-in_electric_vehicle" title=3D"Plug-in el=
ectric vehicle">plug-in electric vehicles</a> and other advanced technology=
 vehicles with the energy consumption<sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equ=
ivalent#cite_note-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> of conventional <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Internal_combustion" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Internal =
combustion">internal combustion</a> vehicles rated in miles per <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_customary_units" title=3D"Unite=
d States customary units">U.S.</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Gallon" title=3D"Gallon">gallon</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-DecodingMPG_2-0" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallo=
n_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-DecodingMPG-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-EPAfueleconomy_3-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-EPAfueleconomy-3"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup>
</p><p>The unit of energy consumed is deemed to be 33.7 <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kilowatt-hour" title=3D"Kilowatt-hour">kilowatt-hours=
</a> without regard to the efficiency of conversion of heat energy into ele=
ctrical energy, also measured in kilowatt-hours (kWh). =20
</p><p>MPGe does not necessarily represent an equivalency in the operating =
costs between alternative fuel vehicles and the MPG rating of internal comb=
ustion engine vehicles due to the wide variation in costs for the fuel sour=
ces regionally<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:6_4-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-=
:6-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_5-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_not=
e-:1-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup> since the EPA assumes prices that represents the nationa=
l averages.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-EPAFEG2017MY_6-0" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cit=
e_note-EPAFEG2017MY-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-:2_7-0" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_eq=
uivalent#cite_note-:2-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Miles per gallon equivalent cost for a=
lternate fuel can be calculated with a simple conversion to the conventiona=
l mpg (miles per gallon, miles/gal). See conversion to MPG by cost below.
</p><p>The MPGe metric was introduced in November 2010 by EPA in the <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monroney_sticker" title=3D"Monroney stic=
ker">Monroney sticker</a> of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/N=
issan_Leaf" title=3D"Nissan Leaf">Nissan Leaf</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Electric_car" title=3D"Electric car">electric car</a> and t=
he <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chevrolet_Volt" title=3D"Chevro=
let Volt">Chevrolet Volt</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plug-=
in_hybrid" title=3D"Plug-in hybrid">plug-in hybrid</a>. The ratings are bas=
ed on EPA's formula, in which 33.7&nbsp;kWh (121&nbsp;MJ) of electricity is=
 equivalent to one (U.S.) gallon of gasoline,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-mpge_8-0" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gall=
on_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-mpge-8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and the energy consumpt=
ion of each vehicle during <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fuel_ec=
onomy_in_automobiles#EPA_testing_procedure:_2008_and_beyond" title=3D"Fuel =
economy in automobiles">EPA's five standard drive cycle tests</a> simulatin=
g varying driving conditions.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-NYTEPA_9-0" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_eq=
uivalent#cite_note-NYTEPA-9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-USAT1124_10-0" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallo=
n_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-USAT1124-10"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[=
</span>10<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> All new cars and l=
ight-duty trucks sold in the U.S. are required to have this label showing t=
he EPA's estimate of fuel economy of the vehicle.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-EPAfue=
leconomy_3-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-EPAfueleconomy-3"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In a joint ruling issued in May 2011 the <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/National_Highway_Traffic_Safety_Administration" title=3D"Nati=
onal Highway Traffic Safety Administration">National Highway Traffic Safety=
 Administration</a> (NHTSA) and EPA established the new requirements for a =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fuel_economy_and_environment_label=
" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Fuel economy and environment label">fuel e=
conomy and environment label</a> that is mandatory for all new passenger ca=
rs and trucks starting with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model_=
year" title=3D"Model year">model year</a> 2013. This ruling uses miles per =
gallon gasoline equivalent for all fuel and advanced technology vehicles av=
ailable in the U.S. market including plug-in hybrids, <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electric_vehicle" title=3D"Electric vehicle">electric v=
ehicles</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flexible-fuel_vehicle=
" title=3D"Flexible-fuel vehicle">flexible-fuel vehicles</a>, <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fuel_cell_vehicle" title=3D"Fuel cell vehicle">=
hydrogen fuel cell vehicle</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Na=
tural_gas_vehicle" title=3D"Natural gas vehicle">natural gas vehicles</a>, =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diesel_engine" title=3D"Diesel eng=
ine">diesel-powered</a> vehicles, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Gasoline_engine" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Gasoline engine">gasoli=
ne-powered</a> vehicles.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-EPA2013_11-0" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equiv=
alent#cite_note-EPA2013-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-GCC2013_12-0" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon=
_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-GCC2013-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</=
span>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In addition to being=
 displayed on new vehicles, fuel economy ratings are used by the <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Department_of_Energy" class=3D"mw-redir=
ect" title=3D"U.S. Department of Energy">U.S. Department of Energy</a> (DOE=
) to publish the annual Fuel Economy Guide; the <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/U.S._Department_of_Transportation" class=3D"mw-redirect" titl=
e=3D"U.S. Department of Transportation">U.S. Department of Transportation</=
a> (DOT) to administer the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corpora=
te_Average_Fuel_Economy" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Corporate Average F=
uel Economy">Corporate Average Fuel Economy</a> (CAFE) program; and the <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internal_Revenue_Service" title=3D"In=
ternal Revenue Service">Internal Revenue Service</a> (IRS) to collect <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gas_guzzler_tax" class=3D"mw-redirect" =
title=3D"Gas guzzler tax">gas guzzler taxes</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-EPAfuel=
economy_3-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M=
iles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-EPAfueleconomy-3"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Fuel economy estimates for window stickers and CAFE standard complia=
nce are different. The EPA MPGe rating shown in the Monroney label is based=
 on the consumption of the on-board energy content stored in the fuel tank =
or in the vehicle's battery, or any other energy source, and only represent=
s the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tank-to-wheel" class=3D"mw-r=
edirect" title=3D"Tank-to-wheel">tank-to-wheel</a> energy consumption. CAFE=
 estimates are based on a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Well-to-=
wheel" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Well-to-wheel">well-to-wheel</a> basi=
s and in the case of liquid fuels and electric drive vehicles also account =
for the energy consumed upstream to produce the fuel or electricity and del=
iver it to the vehicle. Fuel economy for CAFE purposes include an incentive=
 adjustment for alternative fuel vehicles and plug-in electric vehicles whi=
ch results in higher MPGe than those estimated for window stickers.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-AEI2009_13-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-AEI2009-13"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-DOE2000_14-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-=
DOE2000-14"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<meta property=3D"mw:PageProp/toc">
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Background">Background</h2>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</sp=
an><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DMiles_per_gallon=
_gasoline_equivalent&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D1" title=3D"Edit secti=
on: Background"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>]</span></span></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"1988:_Alternative_Motor_Fue=
ls_Act">1988: Alternative Motor Fuels Act</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection=
"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DMiles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent&amp;acti=
on=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: 1988: Alternative Motor F=
uels Act"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</sp=
an></span></div>
<p>The Alternative Motor Fuels Act (AMFA) enacted in 1988<sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-AMFA88_15-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-AMFA88-15"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> prov=
ides Corporate Average Fuel Economy (CAFE) incentives for manufacturing <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alternative_fuel_vehicle" title=3D"Al=
ternative fuel vehicle">alternative fuel vehicles</a> (AFVs) that are power=
ed by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethanol_fuel" title=3D"Ethan=
ol fuel">ethanol</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methanol_fue=
l" title=3D"Methanol fuel">methanol</a>, or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Compressed_natural_gas" title=3D"Compressed natural gas">natural =
gas fuels</a>, either exclusively or in conjunction with gasoline or diesel=
 fuel. These dual-fuel vehicles also are known as <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Flexible-fuel_vehicle" title=3D"Flexible-fuel vehicle">flex=
ible-fuel vehicles</a> (FFVs). To provide incentives for the widespread use=
 of these fuels and to promote the production of AFVs and FFVs, AMFA grants=
 AFV/FFV manufacturers CAFE credits, which allows them to raise their overa=
ll fleet fuel economy levels to comply with the CAFE standards.<sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-NHTS1_16-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-NHTS1-16"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-NHTS2_17-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-NHTS2-17">=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup>
</p><p>Beginning in 1993, manufacturers of qualified AFVs can improve their=
 CAFE estimation by computing the weighted average of the fuel economy when=
 operating on conventional fuel (gasoline and diesel) and when operating on=
 alternative fuel(s).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-NHTS1_16-1" class=3D"reference"><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent=
#cite_note-NHTS1-16"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>16<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=
=3D"Page / location: 9=E2=80=9310">:=E2=80=8A9=E2=80=9310=E2=80=8A</span></=
sup> AMFA provides the following energy content-based equivalency factors:<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-AMFA88_15-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-AMFA88-15"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=3D"Page / location:=
 =C2=A7513">:=E2=80=8A=C2=A7513=E2=80=8A</span></sup>
</p>
<ul><li>1&nbsp;gal (alcohol) =3D 0.15&nbsp;gal (gasoline)</li>
<li>100&nbsp;ft<sup>3</sup> (natural gas) =3D 0.823&nbsp;gal-equivalent (na=
tural gas)
<ul><li>1&nbsp;gal-equivalent (natural gas) =3D 0.15&nbsp;gal (gasoline)</l=
i></ul></li></ul>
<p>A dedicated AFV which operates solely on alcohol would divide the alcoho=
l fuel economy by the energy-equivalency factor of 0.15. As an example, a d=
edicated AFV that achieves 15&nbsp;mpg fuel economy while operating on alco=
hol would have a CAFE calculated as follows:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-NHTS1_16-2"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gal=
lon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-NHTS1-16"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup class=3D"refere=
nce nowrap"><span title=3D"Page / location: 10">:=E2=80=8A10=E2=80=8A</span=
></sup>
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
