</p><p>For FFVs, an assumption is made that the vehicles would operate 50% =
of the time on the alternative fuel and 50% of the time on conventional fue=
l, resulting in a fuel economy that is based on a harmonic average of alter=
native fuel and conventional fuel. For example, for an alternative dual-fue=
l model that achieves 15 miles per gallon operating on an alcohol fuel and =
25&nbsp;mpg on the conventional fuel, the resulting CAFE would be:<sup id=
