<p>MPGe is determined by converting the vehicle consumption per unit distan=
ce, as determined through computer modeling or completion of an actual driv=
ing cycle, from its native units into a gasoline energy equivalent. Example=
s of native units include W=C2=B7h for electric vehicles, kg-<span class=3D=
"chemf nowrap">H<span class=3D"nowrap"><span style=3D"display:inline-block;=
margin-bottom:-0.3em;vertical-align:-0.4em;line-height:1em;font-size:80%;te=
xt-align:left"><sup style=3D"font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical=
-align:baseline"></sup><br><sub style=3D"font-size:inherit;line-height:inhe=
rit;vertical-align:baseline">2</sub></span></span></span> for hydrogen vehi=
cles, gallons for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biodiesel" title=
=3D"Biodiesel">biodiesel</a> or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Li=
quefied_natural_gas" title=3D"Liquefied natural gas">liquefied natural gas<=
/a> vehicles, cubic feet for compressed natural gas vehicles, and <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pound_(mass)" title=3D"Pound (mass)">poun=
ds</a> for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Propane" title=3D"Propa=
ne">propane</a> or Liquefied petroleum gas vehicles. Special cases for spec=
ific alternative fuels are discussed below, but a general formula for MPGe =
is:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 {\text{MPGe}}=3D{\frac {\text{total miles driven}}{\left[{\frac {\text{tot=
al energy of all fuels consumed}}{\text{energy of one gallon of gasoline}}}=
\right]}}=3D{\frac {({\text{total miles driven}})\times ({\text{energy of o=
ne gallon of gasoline}})}{\text{total energy of all fuels consumed}}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
