=3D"Help:Maintenance template removal">Learn how and when to remove this me=
ssage</a></small>)</i></span></div></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The miles p=
er gallon equivalent cost of an alternative fuel vehicle can be calculated =
by a simple formula to directly compare the MPG operating costs (rather tha=
n the energy consumption of MPGe<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:2_7-1" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equ=
ivalent#cite_note-:2-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>) with traditional vehicles since the c=
ost of resources varies substantially from region to region.<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-:1_5-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M=
iles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-:1-5"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-:6_4-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-:6-4"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> For refere=
nce, the complete equation is:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 {\text{MPG}}=3D{\text{mi}}/{\text{gal}}=3D{{\$ \over {\text{gal}}}\div {\$=
 \over {\text{unit}}} \over {\text{capacity(unit)}}}\times {{\text{capacity=
(unit)}} \over [({\text{EnergyQuotient}}\times 100)\div {\text{MPGe}}]\div =
100}}">
