<p>The formula employed by the EPA for calculating their rated MPGe does no=
t account for any fuel or energy consumed upstream such as the generation a=
nd transmission of electrical power, or well-to-wheel life cycle, as EPA's =
comparison with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internal_combustio=
n" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Internal combustion">internal combustion<=
/a> vehicles is made on a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tank-to-=
wheel" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Tank-to-wheel">tank-to-wheel</a> vers=
us battery-to wheel basis.
</p><p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/California_Air_Resource=
s_Board" title=3D"California Air Resources Board">California Air Resources =
Board</a> uses a different <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynamom=
eter" title=3D"Dynamometer">dynamometer</a> testing than EPA, and considers=
 reformulated gasoline sold in that state. For CARB estimates the formula b=
ecomes:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-AEI2009_13-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-A=
EI2009-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
