<p>The new SAE J1711 standard for measuring the exhaust emissions and fuel =
economy of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hybrid_electric_vehicle=
" title=3D"Hybrid electric vehicle">hybrid electric vehicles</a> and plug-i=
n hybrids was approved in July 2010. The recommended procedures for PHEVs w=
ere revised at <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argonne_National_La=
boratory" title=3D"Argonne National Laboratory">Argonne National Laboratory=
</a>, and EPA's new regulation to define PHEV fuel economy reporting protoc=
ol is expected to be based on SAE J1711.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-44" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline=
_equivalent#cite_note-44"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>43<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-45" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_eq=
uivalent#cite_note-45"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>44<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In November 2010 EPA decided to rate e=
lectric mode and gasoline only mode separately, and these are the two figur=
es prominently displayed in the window sticker of the 2011 Chevrolet Volt. =
In electric mode the Volt's rating is estimated with the same formula as an=
 electric car.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-USAT1124_10-2" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cit=
e_note-USAT1124-10"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-AEI2009_13-4" class=3D"r=
eference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasolin=
e_equivalent#cite_note-AEI2009-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The overall or composite fue=
l economy rating combining electricity and gasoline powered are displayed i=
n the Monroney label in a much smaller type, and as part of the comparison =
of the Volt's fuel economy among all vehicles and within <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compact_car" title=3D"Compact car">compact cars</a>.=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-NYT1124_46-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-NYT1124-=
46"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>45<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup> EPA has considered several methodologies for rating the ove=
rall fuel economy of PHEVs, but as of February 2011 EPA has not announced t=
he final methodology that will be applied for the purposes of estimating th=
e new manufacture's 2012=E2=80=932016 Corporate Average Fuel Economy (CAFE)=
 credits for plug-in hybrids.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-AEI2009_13-5" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_=
equivalent#cite_note-AEI2009-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-47" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_ga=
soline_equivalent#cite_note-47"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>46<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Examples_2">Examples</h4><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DMiles_per_gallon_g=
asoline_equivalent&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D12" title=3D"Edit sectio=
n: Examples"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]<=
/span></span></div>
<p>In November 2010 the EPA began including "MPGe" in its new sticker for f=
uel economy and environmental comparisons. The EPA rated the Nissan Leaf el=
ectric car with a combined <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fuel_ec=
onomy_in_automobiles" title=3D"Fuel economy in automobiles">fuel economy</a=
> of 99&nbsp;MPGe,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-NYTEPA_9-2" class=3D"reference"><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#ci=
te_note-NYTEPA-9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and rated the Chevrolet Volt plug-in hybrid wi=
th a combined fuel economy of 93&nbsp;MPGe in <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/All-electric_mode" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"All-electric =
mode">all-electric mode</a>, 37&nbsp;MPG when operating with gasoline only,=
 and an overall fuel economy rating of 60&nbsp;mpg-US (3.9 L/100&nbsp;km) c=
ombining power from electricity and gasoline.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-USAT1124_1=
0-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per=
_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-USAT1124-10"><span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">[</span>10<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-NYT1124_46-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-NYT1124-46"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>45<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p><sup id=3D"cite_ref-GCCEPAVolt_48-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-GCC=
EPAVolt-48"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>47<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup> For both vehicles EPA calculated the MPGe rating un=
der its five-cycle tests using the formula displayed earlier with a convers=
ion factor of 33.7&nbsp;kWh of electricity being the energy equivalent of a=
 gallon of gasoline.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-USAT1124_10-4" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivale=
nt#cite_note-USAT1124-10"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
