<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Life_cycle_assessment">Life=
 cycle assessment</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-edit=
section-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?ti=
tle=3DMiles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D=
18" title=3D"Edit section: Life cycle assessment"><span>edit</span></a><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Pump/Well-to-wheel"><span i=
d=3D"Pump.2FWell-to-wheel"></span>Pump/Well-to-wheel</h3><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DMiles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivale=
nt&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D19" title=3D"Edit section: Pump/Well-to-=
wheel"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span>=
</span></div>
<p>EPA's miles per gallon equivalent metric shown in the window sticker doe=
s not measure a vehicle's full cycle <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Energy_conversion_efficiency" title=3D"Energy conversion efficiency">ene=
rgy efficiency</a> or well-to-wheel life cycle. Rather, the EPA presents MP=
Ge in the same manner as MPG for conventional <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Internal_combustion_engine" title=3D"Internal combustion engine=
">internal combustion engine</a> vehicles as displayed in the <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monroney_sticker" title=3D"Monroney sticker">Mo=
nroney sticker</a>, and in both cases the rating only considers the pump-to=
-wheel or wall-to-wheel energy consumption, i.e. it measures the energy for=
 which the owner usually pays. For EVs the energy cost includes the convers=
ions from AC from the wall used to charge the battery<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Ar=
gonne_40-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mi=
les_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-Argonne-40"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>39<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The EP=
A ratings displayed in window stickers do not account for the energy consum=
ption upstream, which includes the energy or fuel required to generate the =
electricity or to extract and produce the liquid fuel; the energy losses du=
e to power transmission; or the energy consumed for the transportation of t=
he fuel from the well to the station.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-DOE2000_14-7" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_g=
asoline_equivalent#cite_note-DOE2000-14"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-MIT=
_41-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_p=
er_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-MIT-41"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>40<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Petroleum-equivalency_facto=
r_(PEF)_=E2=80=93_a_CAFE_metric"><span id=3D"Petroleum-equivalency_factor_.=
28PEF.29_.E2.80.93_a_CAFE_metric"></span>Petroleum-equivalency factor (PEF)=
 =E2=80=93 a CAFE metric</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"=
mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index=
.php?title=3DMiles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;sec=
tion=3D20" title=3D"Edit section: Petroleum-equivalency factor (PEF) =E2=80=
=93 a CAFE metric"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brack=
et">]</span></span></div>
<p>In 2000 the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Depar=
tment_of_Energy" title=3D"United States Department of Energy">United States=
 Department of Energy</a> (DOE) established the methodology for calculating=
 the petroleum-equivalent fuel economy of electric vehicles based on the we=
ll-to-wheel (WTW) gasoline-equivalent energy content of electricity (<span =
class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-=
mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D=
"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle E_{g}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>E</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>g</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle E_{g}}</annot=
ation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/4e16fa5287303e19370026edc85a044dd74cbc78" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.005ex; width:2.737ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle E_{=
g}}"></span>). The methodology considers the upstream efficiency of the pro=
cesses involved in the two fuel cycles, and considers the national average =
electricity generation and transmission efficiencies because a <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battery_electric_vehicle" title=3D"Battery ele=
ctric vehicle">battery electric vehicle</a> burns its fuel (mainly fossil f=
uels) off-board at the power generation plant.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-DOE2000_1=
4-8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per=
_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-DOE2000-14"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> This methodol=
ogy is used by carmakers to estimate credits into their overall Corporate A=
verage Fuel Economy (CAFE) for manufacturing <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Electric_drive_vehicle" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Electric =
drive vehicle">electric drive vehicles</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-AEI2009_13-6=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_ga=
llon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-AEI2009-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The petroleum equivalent fuel economy of electric vehicles is determ=
ined by the following equations:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-DOE2000_14-9" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoli=
ne_equivalent#cite_note-DOE2000-14"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
