<p>In 2009, the Monroney sticker for the Mini E rated the wall-to-wheel ene=
rgy consumption at 33=E2=80=89/=E2=80=8936&nbsp;kWh/100&nbsp;mi (102.1=E2=
=80=89/=E2=80=8993.6&nbsp;mpg=E2=80=91e) for the city and highway driving c=
ycles, respectively.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Fleming09_91-5" class=3D"reference"=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equival=
ent#cite_note-Fleming09-91"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>90<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The petroleum-equivalent fuel econo=
my is 239&nbsp;MPG<sub>PE</sub>, assuming a 55%/45% urban/highway split.
</p><p>For comparison, the 2017 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ch=
evrolet_Bolt_EV" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Chevrolet Bolt EV">Chevrole=
t Bolt EV</a> has a rated (wall-to-wheel) consumption of 128=E2=80=89/=E2=
=80=89110&nbsp;mpg=E2=80=91e (263=E2=80=89/=E2=80=89306&nbsp;Wh/mi) listed =
on the Monroney sticker for the urban/highway driving cycles, respectively.=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-EPABolt2017_64-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_gallon_gasoline_equivalent#cite_note-EPAB=
olt2017-64"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>63<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup> The petroleum-equivalent fuel economy for the Bolt,=
 using the DoE rule to consider well-to-wall energy losses, is 284&nbsp;MPG=
<sub>PE</sub>, computed using the same 55%/45% urban/highway split.
</p>
